@page "/createcharacter/Pink"
@using Components.Buttons
<h1>The Pink Priest(ess)</h1>

<h4>Kin: The people of Nienna</h4>
<p>Nienna is the Lady of Mercy Acquainted With Grief. It's no surprise, then, that you are particularly strong in areas of willpower and mercy.</p>

<p>Inherent strengths:
    <ul>
        <li>You start with the most willpower.</li>
        <li>You can gain willpower from interacting with any creature, including positive and negative interactions.</li>
        <li>You are exceptionally wise, especially towards the Noldor.</li>
        <li>You have the ability to read the stars and from it divine the mind of Varda, giving you a limited glimpse into the future of any creature born before the sun and moon.</li>
        <li>Commoners naturally revere you.</li>
        <li>Strong in light based magic.</li>
        <li>You are good with any weapon with a Pinky color.</li>
    </ul>
</p>
<p>
    Inherent weaknesses:
    <ul>
        <li>In sunlight and underground, you are weak.</li>
        <li>Any creature created after the sun and moon is a mystery to you.</li>
        <li>Weak to fire, earth and darkness based magic.</li>
        <li>Pretty hopeless with any weapon not made out of polished steel.</li>
    </ul>
</p>
<div>
    <MyButton ButtonText="Back To Color Choices" OnClick="ReturnToColorChoices" />
    <MyButton ButtonText="Choose Pink" OnClick="ChoosePink" />
</div>
@inject NavigationManager NavigationManager
@code {
    private void ReturnToColorChoices()
    {
        NavigationManager.NavigateTo("/createcharacter");
    }
    private void ChoosePink()
    {
        NavigationManager.NavigateTo("/createcharacter");
    }
}
